Barn: Ulla Anne-Marie f. 32, Christina o. Birgitta 43. — Stud:ex. 22, med. kand. 26 o. med. lic. 32, allt i Sthlm. E. läk. v. Sthlms hosp. 29, v. Gbgs hosp. 30, assist :läk. o. tf. und:läk. v. Stocksunds las. med. avd. 31, assist :läk. o. e. läk. v. Varbergs las. 32-33, tf. andre und:-läk. v. Karlskrona las. 33, e. läk. v. Varbergs las. 34, andre und :läk. där 34-35, förste und:läk. där 36-37, dito v. Lidköp. las. kir. avd. 37-41, tf. förste und:läk. v. Sundsvalls las. kir. avd. 41, und :läk. v. Sahlgr. sjukh. kir. avd. i 41-44, sjukst.-läk. i Kungsbacka sed. 45.
translated: Lembke, Sven Samuel, 'sick bay doctor, Kungsbacka, born on 21/6/03 in Matadi, Belgian Congo, to missionary Carl Wilhelm L. and Anna Sofia Broman. Married to Lily Viktoria Frisk. Children: Ulla Anne-Marie born in 1932, Christina and Birgitta born in 1943. — Completed high school in 1922, medical candidate in 1926, and medical licentiate in 1932, all in Stockholm. Started as a medical intern at Stockholm hospital in 1929, Gothenburg hospital in 1930, assistant doctor and temporary deputy physician at Stocksund hospital medical department in 1931, assistant doctor and resident physician at Varberg hospital from 1932-1933, temporary deputy physician at Karlskrona hospital in 1933, resident physician at Varberg hospital in 1934, deputy physician there from 1934-1935, chief deputy physician there from 1936-1937, the same position at Lidköping hospital surgical department from 1937-1941, temporary chief deputy physician at Sundsvall hospital surgical department in 1941, physician at Sahlgr. hospital surgical department from 1941-1944, sick bay doctor in Kungsbacka since 1945.
